<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-11-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-11-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="780" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d780">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 852.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                        the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-11-30"><hi rend="italic">November 30,
                                    1892</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your instruction, numbered
                            970, of the 21st instant, which reached me this morning, with respect to
                            the rights of the United States in the harbor of Pago Pago, I have the
                            honor to acquaint you that I have just had an interview at the foreign
                            office with the Earl of Rosebery, to whom I communicated your views on
                            the subject, by reading to his lordship your instruction, of which I
                            left a copy with him at his request.</p>
                        <p>Lord Rosebery promised to give the matter his prompt attention.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Henry White.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>